label.description: Art historian’s opinion attributing an object to an artist or school and often including commentary on the condition, subject matter, and distinctive features of the work of art.
Record created by Kress Foundation staff summarizing the contemporary condition and previous restoration work of an object.
Key information on the provenance, publication and exhibition history, physical characteristics, and expert opinions for an art object compiled by Kress Foundation staff.
Analytical report sometimes with accompanying X-ray print by conservator/historian Alan Burroughs describing an object’s condition, underpaint, and style, as well as Burroughs’ attribution.
Record of NGA painting conservation work on an object: an examination summary, treatment proposal, treatment report, or scientific analysis report.
Image of an object, in some cases an image documenting an object before, during, or after restoration.
Dealer or collector correspondence that does not relate to a specific acquisition event.
Log recording NGA painting conservation work on an object.
